<h1>Josh Mills</h1>

<h2><a href="/">/now</a>: <a href="http://blog.trueheart78.com/now/">blog.trueheart78.com/now</a></h2>

<h2>Location:</h2>
<p>
Franklin
OH
United States
</p>

<h2>Professional title:</h2>
<p>
Software Developer at CoverMyMeds
</p>

<h2>What do you do?</h2>
<p>
I help make sure that nobody leaves the pharmacy without their medication.
</p>

<h2>Why?</h2>
<p>
I like to help people, so I write software because it allows me to solve problems for people in very interesting ways. Removing friction from people's lives brings me joy.
</p>

<h2>Recent thought or epiphany?</h2>
<p>
It's amazing what you can learn when you let yourself become a newbie again.
</p>

<h2>What should we read?</h2>
<p>
“So Good They Can't Ignore You” by Cal Newport.  “The War of Art” by Steven Pressfield.  “Sex God” by Rob Bell.
</p>

